          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Swapnil Pimpale",
          "email": "spimpale@ddn.com",
          "date": "2014-05-02 17:57:30.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Swapnil Pimpale",
          "email": "spimpale@ddn.com",
          "date": "2014-05-02 17:57:30.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "subject": "LU-9 qos: skeleton for weighted round-robin stripe allocator",
        "message": "LU-9 qos: skeleton for weighted round-robin stripe allocator\n\nThis patch is a rebase of Isami Romanowski's original patch.\n\nIt includes the beginnings of the weighted round-robin\nallocator, which is intended to replace the current two-phase stripe\nallocation (with disjoint round-robin and QoS steps).\n\nCurrently, however, the behavior of the weighted round-robin allocator\nis effectively identical to that of the original round-robin\nallocator. There are some steps needed for the new allocator to start\nshowing improved behavior:\n\n    * Per-pool average weights need to be computed. There is code\n      already which exists to do this, but adding in the op_avg_weight\n      field to struct ost_pool caused bizarre test failures.\n      As of now, the weight threshold during allocation is always set\n      to 0, so the weight of an OST is irrelevant. When these averages\n      are stored, the threshold during allocation should be set to the\n      average OST weight in the pool.\n    * Weight computations are currently done within the allocator code\n      path, which is not necessarily desirable. Better behavior would\n      be to compute weight for an OST at every statfs call.\n\nThe Bugzilla thread about this feature, which can be accessed from the\nJIRA page for the LU-9 ticket, has more information about some of the\ndesired behavior of the new allocator.\n\nSigned-off-by: Swapnil Pimpale <spimpale@ddn.com>\nSigned-off-by: Isami Romanowski <isami@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I0b4395f4f98934d9a05b66c07cba205788e1be92\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
